I had the restaurant cater the office holiday party. They came to my rescue after my initial caterer dropped off the planet. I called and spoke to John. He was hesitant about taking a catering order with less than 48 hour notice, but he agreed.  The food was great!  The chicken was seasoned perfectly. The green sauce and yellow sauce is just fantastic. Oh....we had potatoes that were simply wonderful. Buttery, garlicky wonderfulness. The greens needed a little more salt, but were easily seasoned on my plate. The chicken fried rice is awesome, the corn was great. Plantains were good. It was all just great. But the best part was the way that the caterer handled our order from start to finish.

The chicken is incredible. I ordered delivery from this place three times in a row. Instead of fried (which they have) I ordered the half-chicken. It was juicy and flavorful, with or without the skin. Their fries leave something to be desired, but the salad, especially at lunch time, is fresh and savory. And they put something in it that mskes it not need dressing.  Not to mention, it's enough food for two and a half meals- heats up quite well too.  Add $2 to your order if you like plantsins. Whether you get it with the meal or on the side, you arent getting four slices like at some spots. They fry you at least one big plsntsin or two small ones. Sometimes they are too ripe, or cooked in too much oil but this might be a cultural difference thing rather than a quality thing.  Try the green sauce with your chicken for an extra kick of spice.
